WALKER
v.
The N.C. STATE BOARD OF DENTAL EXAMINERS 95PA16-1 Supreme Court of North Carolina. September 15, 2016 Ryan McKaig, Attorney at Law, Elizabeth Brooks Scherer, Attorney at Law, Raleigh, for Walker, Cynthia (D.D.S.). Carolin Bakewell, Attorney at Law, Matthew W. Sawchak, Attorney at Law, Stephen D. Feldman, Attorney at Law, Troy D. Shelton, Attorney at Law, Paul M. Cox, Attorney at Law, Raleigh, for The N.C. State Board of Dental Examiners. Clinton R. Pinyan, Attorney at Law, Greensboro, for N.C. Board of Pharmacy

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 14th of September 2016 by the North Carolina Board of Pharmacy for leave to file Amicus Curiae Brief:

"Motion Allowed by order of the Court in conference, this the 15th of September 2016."

Unless already submitted, the Amicus Brief shall be submitted to the court within the times allowed and in the manner provided by Appellate Rule 28(i).
